The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Metro Railway will run eight extra trains daily on November 3 and 4 and from November 8 to 12. Metro usually runs 214 rakes daily.    Shibnath Kundu, 55, an employee of the telecommunication department of Eastern Railway, was found dead in his office at Belanagar station with a rope around his neck on Tuesday morning. GRP sources said Kundu was on night duty on Monday.     A fire broke out in a sofa repairing shop at Topsia on Tuesday evening. Three tenders fought the flames at 63/1 Gulam Jilani Khan Road. Firemen suspect a short-circuit led to the blaze. Another fire broke out at Fort William Jute Mill in Shibpur on Tuesday evening. Three tenders doused the flames. Nobody was injured.    Services on Eastern Railways Sealdah (Main) section were disrupted from 7.14am to 8.20am on Tuesday after a branch fell on the overhead wire near Sodepur. Three local trains were cancelled.    Sujit Das, 43, a resident of Chetla Lock Gate, was hit by an unidentified car on the Bypass-Park Circus connector at 10.30am on Tuesday. He was admitted to National Medical College. Another unidentified vehicle hit pedestrian Rasamoy Kar, 40, near the Hudco crossing at 12.50pm. Kar, a resident of Dankuni, was taken to Manicktala ESI hospital.                                                                                                                                               
